 "context": {
  "patient_ref": "MRN6756332150",
  "text": "# Adrenal Incidentaloma Evaluation\n\n## Context\n\nThe current date and time is 2024-03-11T23:20:00. You are an endocrinologist at an academic medical center (Practitioner ID: dr-gabriel-ingram). A CT imaging report has been flagged for your review showing an incidental adrenal finding in a patient (MRN6756332150) who is followed for other medical conditions.\n\n## Your Task\n\n1. **Review the patient's clinical data**\n   - Retrieve relevant imaging reports documenting the adrenal finding\n   - Review current diagnoses, paying attention to cardiovascular comorbidities\n   - Assess current medications and blood pressure control\n   - Review available laboratory data including electrolytes and metabolic panel\n\n2. **Determine appropriate hormonal workup**\n   - Identify which biochemical tests are indicated based on the mass characteristics\n   - Consider how the patient's comorbidities may warrant additional screening tests beyond standard incidentaloma workup\n   - Include clear instructions for any tests requiring specific patient preparation\n\n3. **Order appropriate diagnostic studies**\n   - Place orders for indicated laboratory tests\n   - Arrange follow-up imaging within 1-2 months for mass characterization\n\n4. **Document your evaluation and plan**\n   - Summarize the clinical findings and rationale for recommended workup\n   - Include contingency planning for abnormal results\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- Adrenal incidentaloma assessment and management plan saved to `/workspace/output/adrenal_assessment.txt`\n"
 },
